Files:
- platform/cli/src/commands/plugin.ts (add post-filtering to npmSearchPlugins)

Context:
The server's searchNpmPlugins in platform/mcp-server/src/plugin-management.ts already has the fix (commit 439ec522). It uses extractShortName and filters:
```
if (query) {
  const q = query.toLowerCase();
  return results.filter(
    r => extractShortName(r.name).toLowerCase().includes(q) || r.description.toLowerCase().includes(q),
  );
}
```

The CLI's npmSearchPlugins at line 353-372 does the same npm search but has no post-filtering:
```
const npmSearchPlugins = (query?: string): NpmSearchPackage[] => {
  const searchTerm = query ? `keywords:opentabs-plugin ${query}` : 'keywords:opentabs-plugin';
  const result = spawnProcessSync(platformExec('npm'), ['search', searchTerm, '--json']);
  if (result.exitCode !== 0) return [];
  try {
    const entries = JSON.parse(result.stdout.trim()) as NpmSearchJsonEntry[];
    return entries.map(entry => ({
      name: entry.name,
      description: entry.description,
      version: entry.version,
      publisher: entry.publisher?.username
        ? { username: entry.publisher.username }
        : entry.author?.name
          ? { username: entry.author.name }
          : undefined,
    }));
  } catch {
    return [];
  }
};
```

Changes:
1. Add a helper to extract the short name:
```
const extractShortName = (name: string): string => (name.split('/').pop() ?? name).replace(/^opentabs-plugin-/, '');
```

2. After the `entries.map(...)` call, add post-filtering when a query is provided:
```
if (query) {
  const q = query.toLowerCase();
  return results.filter(
    r => extractShortName(r.name).toLowerCase().includes(q) || (r.description ?? '').toLowerCase().includes(q),
  );
}
return results;
```

Note: The CLI's description field is `string | undefined` (from NpmSearchJsonEntry.description which is optional), so use `(r.description ?? '')` for the filter.

Constraints:
- Do NOT share code between CLI and MCP server — they are separate packages with different dependencies, the duplication is intentional
- The PLUGIN_PREFIX constant already exists in the file (imported from shared) but extractShortName is simpler and self-contained
- The post-filtering should only apply to the npm search results, NOT to the direct lookup candidates (buildDirectLookupCandidates results at line 381 are already targeted by name)
